I just want to give you a heads up.

1259
01:29:05.943 --> 01:29:09.064
They're going to start sending
a few people home now.

1260
01:29:11.464 --> 01:29:12.468
Now?

1261
01:29:12.543 --> 01:29:14.431
Yes. Sam. No loose ends.

1262
01:29:20.583 --> 01:29:21.871
Of course.

1263
01:29:23.144 --> 01:29:25.031
And for what it's worth.

1264
01:29:26.024 --> 01:29:27.628
you're still good.

1265
01:29:30.424 --> 01:29:33.544
Yeah. I guess someone upstairs
really likes you.

1266
01:30:25.783 --> 01:30:26.862
Sam.

1267
01:30:28.263 --> 01:30:29.746
Please. sit.

1268
01:30:29.823 --> 01:30:32.311
Congratulations are clearly in order.

1269
01:30:33.022 --> 01:30:35.150
They did the best they could.

1270
01:30:35.943 --> 01:30:39.707
You did a hell of a job.
And I thank you for it. Come on. sit.

1271
01:30:40.422 --> 01:30:41.666
Excuse me for eating.

1272
01:30:43.462 --> 01:30:45.143
but it's been a long day.

1273
01:30:45.222 --> 01:30:48.146
- Can I get you something?
- No. nothing. Thanks.

1274
01:30:51.262 --> 01:30:53.106
So. what can I do for you?

1275
01:30:53.182 --> 01:30:54.623
I want out.

1276
01:30:56.102 --> 01:30:57.947
I'm done. I want out.

1277
01:31:00.182 --> 01:31:02.986
- It's been a very difficult day for everyone.
- I need you to release my options.

1278
01:31:02.987 --> 01:31:05.541
if they're worth anything after today.
I want my bonus. I'm out.

1279
01:31:05.542 --> 01:31:08.303
You'll get your bonus. your options.
and keep your current base.

1280
01:31:08.382 --> 01:31:11.666
But I need you to stay with me
for the next 24 months. okay?

1281
01:31:15.462 --> 01:31:17.381
Oh. come on. Sam.

1282
01:31:17.382 --> 01:31:18.506
Put a smile on your face.

1283
01:31:18.507 --> 01:31:21.381
You did some good today.
You said that yourself.

1284
01:31:21.382 --> 01:31:24.590
Do you know. I'm starting to feel
a little better about this whole thing.

1285
01:31:26.662 --> 01:31:29.423
You're one of the luckiest guys
in the world. Sam.

1286
01:31:29.501 --> 01:31:31.269
Could have been digging
ditches all these years.

1287
01:31:32.422 --> 01:31:33.710
That's true.

1288
01:31:33.782 --> 01:31:37.503
And if I had. at least there'd be
some holes in the ground to show for it.

1289
01:31:39.142 --> 01:31:40.141
Jesus.

1290
01:31:40.142 --> 01:31:43.470
I just don't know
how we fucked this up quite so much.

1291
01:31:47.302 --> 01:31:49.266
When did you start feeling
so sorry for yourself?

1292
01:31:49.267 --> 01:31:51.061
It's unbearable. What?

1293
01:31:51.622 --> 01:31:54.862
So you think we might have put
a few people out of business today.

1294
01:31:54.942 --> 01:31:56.742
That's all for naught.

1295
01:31:57.621 --> 01:32:01.505
But you've been doing that every day
for almost 40 years. Sam.

1296
01:32:02.741 --> 01:32:06.506
And if this is all for naught.
then so is everything out there.

1297
01:32:09.141 --> 01:32:10.789
It's just money.

1298
01:32:11.381 --> 01:32:12.909
It's made up.

1299
01:32:13.861 --> 01:32:15.225
pieces of paper with pictures on it

1300
01:32:15.301 --> 01:32:19.065
so that we don't have to kill each other
just to get something to eat.

1301
01:32:19.621 --> 01:32:21.062
It's not wrong.

1302
01:32:21.541 --> 01:32:24.585
And it's certainly no different today
than it's ever been.

1303
01:32:25.901 --> 01:32:28.662
1637. 1797.

1304
01:32:28.741 --> 01:32:32.941
1819.1837. 1857.1884.

1305
01:32:34.781 --> 01:32:36.745
1901. 1907.

1306
01:32:37.181 --> 01:32:40.105
1929. 1937. 1974.

1307
01:32:40.861 --> 01:32:43.785
1987. Jesus.
Didn't that fucker fuck me up good.

1308
01:32:43.861 --> 01:32:46.862
1992. 1997. 2000.
and whatever we want to call this.

1309
01:32:46.941 --> 01:32:50.705
It's all just the same thing. over and over.
We can't help ourselves.

1310
01:32:51.500 --> 01:32:54.980
And you and I can't control it

1311
01:32:54.981 --> 01:32:57.742
or stop it or even slow it.

1312
01:32:57.820 --> 01:32:59.981
Or even ever so slightly alter it.

1313
01:33:00.901 --> 01:33:02.384
We just react.

1314
01:33:03.221 --> 01:33:05.425
And we make a lot of money
if we get it right.

1315
01:33:05.500 --> 01:33:08.349
And we get left by the side of the road
if we get it wrong.

1316
01:33:08.421 --> 01:33:10.188
And there have always been
and there always will be

1317
01:33:10.261 --> 01:33:11.865
the same percentage of winners and losers.

1318
01:33:11.940 --> 01:33:13.228
happy fucks and sad sacks.

1319
01:33:13.301 --> 01:33:15.985
fat cats and starving dogs in this world.

1320
01:33:17.941 --> 01:33:18.988
Yeah.

1321
01:33:20.421 --> 01:33:23.339
There may be more of us today
than there's ever been.

1322
01:33:23.340 --> 01:33:26.625
But the percentages.
they stay exactly the same.

1323
01:33:45.340 --> 01:33:49.059
I'll do it. John.
but not because of your little speech.

1324
01:33:49.060 --> 01:33:51.189
But because I need the money.

1325
01:33:52.500 --> 01:33:56.942
Hard to believe after all these years.
but I need the money.

1326
01:34:00.260 --> 01:34:01.427
This is the executive dining room.

1327
01:34:01.500 --> 01:34:04.020
- Do you want coffee or tea?
- No.

1328
01:34:08.060 --> 01:34:09.947
You gonna keep the kid?

1329
01:34:11.380 --> 01:34:13.704
Keep him? He's getting promoted.

1330
01:34:14.500 --> 01:34:16.267
It's all hands on deck now. Sam.

1331
01:34:16.340 --> 01:34:18.664
There's going to be a lot of money
to be made coming out of this mess.

1332
01:34:18.665 --> 01:34:22.228
and we're gonna need
all the brains we can get around here.

1333
01:35:42.979 --> 01:35:44.267
Hello.

1334
01:35:45.659 --> 01:35:47.307
I've called the police.

1335
01:35:47.379 --> 01:35:48.503
Mary.

1336
01:35:49.139 --> 01:35:50.579
- Sam.
- Yep.

1337
01:35:53.299 --> 01:35:54.979
What are you doing?

1338
01:36:10.299 --> 01:36:12.186
Sam. what are you doing?

1339
01:36:14.218 --> 01:36:15.702
Ella died.

1340
01:36:40.258 --> 01:36:44.546
I was driving home from the vet
and I couldn't think of where else to go.

1341
01:36:45.978 --> 01:36:48.663
- She belongs here.
- I know.

1342
01:36:48.738 --> 01:36:50.942
But. Sam. you don't live here anymore.

1343
01:36:56.858 --> 01:36:58.505
Are you all right?

1344
01:36:59.618 --> 01:37:01.462
You don't look so good.

1345
01:37:03.178 --> 01:37:05.262
Yeah. it's been a rough day
all the way around.

1346
01:37:05.338 --> 01:37:07.063
I know. Sammy called.

1347
01:37:07.458 --> 01:37:08.462
Is he all right?

1348
01:37:08.538 --> 01:37:11.462
They got hammered. but they got out alive.

1349
01:37:11.537 --> 01:37:12.585
Good.

1350
01:37:20.098 --> 01:37:22.421
Well. I'm gonna go back inside

1351
01:37:24.498 --> 01:37:25.906
and go back to bed.

1352
01:37:27.057 --> 01:37:29.818
The alarm is on. so don't try and break in.

1353
01:37:38.817 --> 01:37:40.617
Take care of yourself.
